# Git Workflow

Git commands that open interactive editors will block agent execution. Always use non-interactive flags.

**Rule:** Set `GIT_EDITOR=true` before any git operation that might open an editor.

```bash
export GIT_EDITOR=true              # Commit message editor
export GIT_SEQUENCE_EDITOR=true     # Interactive rebase editor
```

| Operation | Non-Interactive Command |
|---|---|
| Commit | `git commit -m "message"` |
| Amend | `git commit --amend --no-edit` |
| Rebase | `GIT_EDITOR=true git rebase origin/main` |
| Interactive rebase | `GIT_SEQUENCE_EDITOR=true git rebase -i --autosquash <base>` |
| Cherry-pick | `GIT_EDITOR=true git cherry-pick <sha>` |
| Merge | `git merge <branch> -m "message"` |
| Tag | `git tag -a v1.0.0 -m "message"` |

Use `git push --force-with-lease` (not `--force`). If stuck, `git rebase --abort` and retry with `GIT_EDITOR=true`.
